        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): suppress fatal error completion announce",
        "body": "Fixes #42243.\n\n## Summary\n- short-circuit normal cron completion delivery only when an isolated run resolves to a fatal structured `isError` payload\n- keep controlled fatal failure signals on the existing delivery path, preserving existing cron behavior\n- keep the cron run marked as error with diagnostics and delivery trace state, but avoid direct announce fallback with provider error JSON\n- rebase the PR on current `origin/main` so the branch no longer depends on the old base\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: A cron isolated-agent run with `delivery.mode=announce` and a fatal structured `isError` payload should not send provider error JSON to the configured channel as a normal cron completion message. Controlled synthesized fatal failure signals should still use the existing delivery path.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on macOS rebased on current `origin/main` at commit `2e6ca9f703`, using the repo cron test runner against the actual isolated-agent delivery policy path.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/cron/isolated-agent/run.message-tool-policy.test.ts src/cron/isolated-agent/run.interim-retry.test.ts` and `git diff --check`.\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output): Copied terminal output from the local checkout:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/cron/isolated-agent/run.message-tool-policy.test.ts src/cron/isolated-agent/run.interim-retry.test.ts\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  37 passed (37)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 17.90s\n\n$ git diff --check\n# no output\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: The new fatal structured error payload path skips `dispatchCronDelivery`, while the existing synthesized fatal failure signal case still dispatches through the controlled delivery path.\n- What was not tested: A live Discord or Telegram send with real channel credentials was not run locally; the changed decision point is before external channel transport.\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): Before the patch, fatal structured `isError` payloads could continue into normal announce completion delivery and expose provider error JSON.\n\n## Testing\n- node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/cron/isolated-agent/run.message-tool-policy.test.ts src/cron/isolated-agent/run.interim-retry.test.ts\n- git diff --check",
